sentences: Together with his friend and collaborator Bert Kaempfert, he was posthumously inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 1993.
There he became musical director of the Belgrade Radio Orchestra, until he left Yugoslavia in 1952.
He produced three albums of instrumentals with his own orchestra, including Music to Soothe That Tiger (1964), in a highly romantic style.
He died of cancer in Basel, Switzerland, in 1979 at the age of 57.

sentences: Herbert "Herb" Rehbein (15 April 1922 – 28 July 1979) was a German songwriter, composer and arranger of light orchestral music.
He also won the competition to provide the Olympic Fanfare for the 1972 Summer Olympics.
